HEADWORD: Lightwood
<hw>Light"wood`</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"w⟦oocr⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Pine wood abounding in pitch, used for torches in the Southern
United States; pine knots, dry sticks, and the like, for kindling a fire
quickly or making a blaze.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lighty</ent>⟦br⟧
